76978e-06, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2020 Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 3469, \"to\": 3489}, {\"ngram\": \"pandemic reasons\", \"from\": 3501, \"to\": 3517}, {\"ngram\": \"58 percent\", \"from\": 3538, \"to\": 3548}, {\"ngram\": \"the prime-time screen\", \"from\": 3552, \"to\": 3573}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 3577, \"to\": 3582}, {\"ngram\": \"a paper\", \"from\": 3597, \"to\": 3604}, {\"ngram\": \"theInternational Journal\", \"from\": 3618, \"to\": 3642}, {\"ngram\": \"Sport Communication\", \"from\": 3646, \"to\": 3665}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Call this the representation theory of why women love the Olympics: Put women on TV, and female audiences will watch.\", \"from\": 3668, \"to\": 3785, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the representation theory\", \"from\": 3678, \"to\": 3703}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 3711, \"to\": 3716}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3722, \"to\": 3734}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 3740, \"to\": 3745}, {\"ngram\": \"TV\", \"from\": 3749, \"to\": 3751}, {\"ngram\": \"female audiences\", \"from\": 3757, \"to\": 3773}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But that explanation only goes so far.\", \"from\": 3786, \"to\": 3824, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that explanation\", \"from\": 3790, \"to\": 3806}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unsporty eggheads like me do not care about non-Olympic sports, regardless of the sex of the participants.\", \"from\": 3825, \"to\": 3931, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3869, \"end\": 3887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"non-Olympic sports\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_sports\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Unsporty eggheads\", \"from\": 3825, \"to\": 3842}, {\"ngram\": \"the sex\", \"from\": 3903, \"to\": 3910}, {\"ngram\": \"the participants\", \"from\": 3914, \"to\": 3930}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For me, the WNBA holds no more appeal than the NBA.\", \"from\": 3932, \"to\": 3983, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3944, \"end\": 3948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7825386019728664e-22, \"text\": \"WNBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 3979, \"end\": 3982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 0.99999955394388, \"rank\": 4.460558532234435e-07, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no more appeal\", \"from\": 3955, \"to\": 3969}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So what do I see in the Olympics?\", \"from\": 3984, \"to\": 4017, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 4004, \"to\": 4016}]}, {\"sentence\": \"First, it must be said that I see pageantry and good outfits.\", \"from\": 4019, \"to\": 4080, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"pageantry\", \"from\": 4053, \"to\": 4062}, {\"ngram\": \"good outfits\", \"from\": 4067, \"to\": 4079}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Recall that the Olympics are one oftwomajor sporting events on NBC that draw more female viewers than male.\", \"from\": 4081, \"to\": 4188, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4144, \"end\": 4147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999968759369635, \"rank\": 3.120054009876978e-06, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 4093, \"to\": 4105}, {\"ngram\": \"one oftwomajor sporting events\", \"from\": 4110, \"to\": 4140}, {\"ngram\": \"more female viewers\", \"from\": 4158, \"to\": 4177}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The other is the Kentucky Derby, an ostentatious-hat convention that happens to take place beside a horse race.\", \"from\": 4189, \"to\": 4300, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4206, \"end\": 4220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kentucky_Derby\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1197015555148437e-18, \"text\": \"Kentucky Derby\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kentucky_Derby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kentucky_Derby\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an ostentatious-hat convention\", \"from\": 4222, \"to\": 4252}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 4274, \"to\": 4279}, {\"ngram\": \"a horse race\", \"from\": 4287, \"to\": 4299}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I can not be alone in watching the Olympics partly to see what Stella McCartney designed for the British team and to gawk at the spectacle of equestrian jumps in Versailles.\", \"from\": 4301, \"to\": 4474, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4364, \"end\": 4380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stella_McCartney\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stella McCartney\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q3501317\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stella_McCartney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stella_McCartney\"}, {\"begin\": 4398, \"end\": 4405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.956621901143778, \"rank\": 0.04219290103360973, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 4443, \"end\": 4453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.9999999882402336, \"rank\": 1.1759987062422737e-08, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}, {\"begin\": 4463, \"end\": 4473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"score\": 0.9999994304991363, \"rank\": 5.695014478380077e-07, \"text\": \"Versailles\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 4332, \"to\": 4344}, {\"ngram\": \"the spectacle\", \"from\": 4426, \"to\": 4439}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Second, I see a competition that more closely resembles the worlds in which women feel comfortable and thrive.\", \"from\": 4476, \"to\": 4586, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a competition\", \"from\": 4490, \"to\": 4503}, {\"ngram\": \"the worlds\", \"from\": 4532, \"to\": 4542}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 4552, \"to\": 4557}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(I have already started generalizing wildly about half the human race, so let me keep going.)\", \"from\": 4587, \"to\": 4680, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"wildly about half the human race\", \"from\": 4624, \"to\": 4656}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Women tend to dobetterin school than men, and the Olympics-with their elitism, insistence on classic Greek origins, and stuffy, corrupt bureaucracies-have a lot in common with academia.\", \"from\": 4681, \"to\": 4866, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4774, \"end\": 4787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greek\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"classic Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greek\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greek\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Women\", \"from\": 4681, \"to\": 4686}, {\"ngram\": \"school\", \"from\": 4706, \"to\": 4712}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 4718, \"to\": 4721}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 4727, \"to\": 4739}, {\"ngram\": \"their elitism\", \"from\": 4745, \"to\": 4758}, {\"ngram\": \"insistence\", \"from\": 4760, \"to\": 4770}, {\"ngram\": \"stuffy, corrupt bureaucracies\", \"from\": 4801, \"to\": 4830}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 4836, \"to\": 4841}, {\"ngram\": \"academia\", \"from\": 4857, \"to\": 4865}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In many marquee Olympic events, such as figure skating, athletes literally get grades.\", \"from\": 4867, \"to\": 4953, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many marquee Olympic events\", \"from\": 4870, \"to\": 4897}, {\"ngram\": \"figure skating\", \"from\": 4907, \"to\": 4921}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 4923, \"to\": 4931}, {\"ngram\": \"grades\", \"from\": 4946, \"to\": 4952}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Women are also shown in polls to bemore supportivethan men of multilateral organizations, and the International Olympic Committee is basically the United Nations of sports.\", \"from\": 4954, \"to\": 5126, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5052, \"end\": 5083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 5101, \"end\": 5115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"score\": 0.9992389837228814, \"rank\": 0.0007615958635258864, \"text\": \"United Nations\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Women\", \"from\": 4954, \"to\": 4959}, {\"ngram\": \"polls\", \"from\": 4978, \"to\": 4983}, {\"ngram\": \"supportivethan men\", \"from\": 4994, \"to\": 5012}, {\"ngram\": \"multilateral organizations\", \"from\": 5016, \"to\": 5042}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 5119, \"to\": 5125}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Women also visit museums and art galleries more than men do,according to visitor data.\", \"from\": 5127, \"to\": 5213, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Women\", \"from\": 5127, \"to\": 5132}, {\"ngram\": \"museums\", \"from\": 5144, \"to\": 5151}, {\"ngram\": \"art galleries\", \"from\": 5156, \"to\": 5169}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 5180, \"to\": 5183}, {\"ngram\": \"visitor data\", \"from\": 5200, \"to\": 5212}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics offer a synthesized, highly curated overview-one might sayexhibition-of every imaginable sport.\", \"from\": 5214, \"to\": 5322, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 5214, \"to\": 5226}, {\"ngram\": \"a synthesized, highly curated overview-one\", \"from\": 5233, \"to\": 5275}, {\"ngram\": \"every imaginable sport\", \"from\": 5299, \"to\": 5321}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, I see an idea of athletic achievement that has more to do with excellence than with dominating an opponent.\", \"from\": 5324, \"to\": 5440, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an idea\", \"from\": 5339, \"to\": 5346}, {\"ngram\": \"athletic achievement\", \"from\": 5350, \"to\": 5370}, {\"ngram\": \"excellence\", \"from\": 5396, \"to\": 5406}, {\"ngram\": \"an opponent\", \"from\": 5428, \"to\": 5439}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When people say they love watching sports, they usually mean sports with balls-football, basketball.\", \"from\": 5442, \"to\": 5542, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 5447, \"to\": 5453}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 5477, \"to\": 5483}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 5503, \"to\": 5509}, {\"ngram\": \"balls\", \"from\": 5515, \"to\": 5520}, {\"ngram\": \"football\", \"from\": 5521, \"to\": 5529}, {\"ngram\": \"basketball\", \"from\": 5531, \"to\": 5541}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports with balls (or, in the case of hockey, pucks-close enough) are zero-sum.\", \"from\": 5543, \"to\": 5622, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sports\", \"from\": 5543, \"to\": 5549}, {\"ngram\": \"balls\", \"from\": 5555, \"to\": 5560}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 5569, \"to\": 5577}, {\"ngram\": \"hockey\", \"from\": 5581, \"to\": 5587}, {\"ngram\": \"zero-sum\", \"from\": 5613, \"to\": 5621}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You cannot play soccer or tennis without an opponent, and you can succeed only at their expense-not merely by outperforming them, but by causing them to fail.\", \"from\": 5623, \"to\": 5781, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"soccer\", \"from\": 5639, \"to\": 5645}, {\"ngram\": \"tennis\", \"from\": 5649, \"to\": 5655}, {\"ngram\": \"an opponent\", \"from\": 5664, \"to\": 5675}, {\"ngram\": \"their expense\", \"from\": 5705, \"to\": 5718}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These are not only sports; they are alsogames: socially constructed contests thatproduce winners and losers-a quality that excites crowds-and that are based on ultimatelyarbitraryrules.\", \"from\": 5782, \"to\": 5967, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 5801, \"to\": 5807}, {\"ngram\": \"alsogames\", \"from\": 5818, \"to\": 5827}, {\"ngram\": \"socially constructed contests\", \"from\": 5829, \"to\": 5858}, {\"ngram\": \"winners\", \"from\": 5871, \"to\": 5878}, {\"ngram\": \"losers\", \"from\": 5883, \"to\": 5889}, {\"ngram\": \"a quality\", \"from\": 5890, \"to\": 5899}, {\"ngram\": \"crowds\", \"from\": 5913, \"to\": 5919}, {\"ngram\": \"ultimatelyarbitraryrules\", \"from\": 5942, \"to\": 5966}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From the January/February 2014 issue: The accidental spectator's guide to improving sports During the Olympic season, the ball sports that usually monopolize media attention lose importance.\", \"from\": 5969, \"to\": 6160, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the January/February 2014 issue\", \"from\": 5974, \"to\": 6005}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 6053, \"to\": 6059}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic season\", \"from\": 6067, \"to\": 6085}, {\"ngram\": \"the ball sports\", \"from\": 6087, \"to\": 6102}, {\"ngram\": \"media attention\", \"from\": 6127, \"to\": 6142}, {\"ngram\": \"importance\", \"from\": 6148, \"to\": 6158}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics may be called the Games, but what sets them apart is that they showcase sports that are not in fact games: artistic expressions such as gymnastics and figure skating, races such as track and field and swimming-sports that are not only sports but also survival skills or dances.\", \"from\": 6161, \"to\": 6451, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 6161, \"to\": 6173}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 6188, \"to\": 6197}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 6246, \"to\": 6252}, {\"ngram\": \"fact games\", \"from\": 6269, \"to\": 6279}, {\"ngram\": \"artistic expressions\", \"from\": 6281, \"to\": 6301}, {\"ngram\": \"gymnastics\", \"from\": 6310, \"to\": 6320}, {\"ngram\": \"figure skating\", \"from\": 6325, \"to\": 6339}, {\"ngram\": \"races\", \"from\": 6341, \"to\": 6346}, {\"ngram\": \"track\", \"from\": 6355, \"to\": 6360}, {\"ngram\": \"field\", \"from\": 6365, \"to\": 6370}, {\"ngram\": \"swimming-sports\", \"from\": 6375, \"to\": 6390}, {\"ngram\": \"not only sports\", \"from\": 6400, \"to\": 6415}, {\"ngram\": \"survival skills\", \"from\": 6425, \"to\": 6440}, {\"ngram\": \"dances\", \"from\": 6444, \"to\": 6450}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You \\\"play\\\" soccer and volleyball, but you do not play running or swimming or skiing; you simply run, swim, or ski.\", \"from\": 6452, \"to\": 6566, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"soccer\", \"from\": 6463, \"to\": 6469}, {\"ngram\": \"volleyball\", \"from\": 6474, \"to\": 6484}, {\"ngram\": \"running\", \"from\": 6506, \"to\": 6513}, {\"ngram\": \"swimming\", \"from\": 6517, \"to\": 6525}, {\"ngram\": \"skiing\", \"from\": 6529, \"to\": 6535}, {\"ngram\": \"swim\", \"from\": 6553, \"to\": 6557}, {\"ngram\": \"ski\", \"from\": 6562, \"to\": 6565}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These activities present not a problem to solve or an opponent to overcome so much as a test of what the human body can do.\", \"from\": 6567, \"to\": 6690, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These activities\", \"from\": 6567, \"to\": 6583}, {\"ngram\": \"not a problem\", \"from\": 6592, \"to\": 6605}, {\"ngram\": \"an opponent\", \"from\": 6618, \"to\": 6629}, {\"ngram\": \"a test\", \"from\": 6653, \"to\": 6659}, {\"ngram\": \"the human body\", \"from\": 6668, \"to\": 6682}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Citius, altius, fortius\\\" is the Olympic slogan: \\\"Faster, higher, stronger.\\\"\", \"from\": 6691, \"to\": 6767, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6692, \"end\": 6715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_symbols\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Citius, altius, fortius\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_symbols\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_symbols\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic slogan\", \"from\": 6720, \"to\": 6738}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Part of what draws me, an otherwise sports-averse woman, to the Olympics is the pursuit of perfection that is not intrinsically competitive.\", \"from\": 6769, \"to\": 6909, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an otherwise sports-averse woman\", \"from\": 6792, \"to\": 6824}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 6829, \"to\": 6841}, {\"ngram\": \"the pursuit\", \"from\": 6845, \"to\": 6856}, {\"ngram\": \"perfection\", \"from\": 6860, \"to\": 6870}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Of course, Olympic athletes are trying to win.\", \"from\": 6910, \"to\": 6956, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympic athletes\", \"from\": 6921, \"to\": 6937}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not everyone gets a medal.\", \"from\": 6957, \"to\": 6983, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Not everyone\", \"from\": 6957, \"to\": 6969}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 6975, \"to\": 6982}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But runners and swimmers and so on are not bound to their opponents in the same way that ball-sport players are.\", \"from\": 6984, \"to\": 7096, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"runners\", \"from\": 6988, \"to\": 6995}, {\"ngram\": \"swimmers\", \"from\": 7000, \"to\": 7008}, {\"ngram\": \"their opponents\", \"from\": 7036, \"to\": 7051}, {\"ngram\": \"the same way\", \"from\": 7055, \"to\": 7067}, {\"ngram\": \"ball-sport players\", \"from\": 7073, \"to\": 7091}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Anita DeFrantz, an American bronze medalist for rowing in the Montreal 1976 Olympics, told me that her coach always instructed the team to forget the boats they were racing against, to keep their eyes on the lane.\", \"from\": 7097, \"to\": 7310, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7097, \"end\": 7111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anita_DeFrantz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anita DeFrantz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anita_DeFrantz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anita_DeFrantz\"}, {\"begin\": 7116, \"end\": 7124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999974138615261, \"rank\": 2.0005495267071857e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Montreal 1976 Olympics\", \"from\": 7155, \"to\": 7181}, {\"ngram\": \"her coach\", \"from\": 7196, \"to\": 7205}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 7224, \"to\": 7232}, {\"ngram\": \"the boats\", \"from\": 7243, \"to\": 7252}, {\"ngram\": \"their eyes\", \"from\": 7287, \"to\": 7297}, {\"ngram\": \"the lane\", \"from\": 7301, \"to\": 7309}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This proved hard because she wanted to win, and indeed, she sometimes could not stop herself from peeking at the other boats during the competition.\", \"from\": 7311, \"to\": 7459, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the other boats\", \"from\": 7420, \"to\": 7435}, {\"ngram\": \"the competition\", \"from\": 7443, \"to\": 7458}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But she was at her best when she followed her coach's advice and focused her attention on the act itself.\", \"from\": 7460, \"to\": 7565, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her coach's advice\", \"from\": 7502, \"to\": 7520}, {\"ngram\": \"her attention\", \"from\": 7533, \"to\": 7546}, {\"ngram\": \"the act\", \"from\": 7550, \"to\": 7557}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's the thrill of the boat when it's up to speed, winding up in the water, and you can hear the bubbles running down,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 7566, \"to\": 7696, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the thrill\", \"from\": 7572, \"to\": 7582}, {\"ngram\": \"the boat\", \"from\": 7586, \"to\": 7594}, {\"ngram\": \"the water\", \"from\": 7632, \"to\": 7641}, {\"ngram\": \"the bubbles\", \"from\": 7660, \"to\": 7671}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And when it's going that fast, there is just nothing like it.\\\"\", \"from\": 7697, \"to\": 7760, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just nothing\", \"from\": 7738, \"to\": 7750}]}, {\"sentence\": \"DeFrantz has dedicated her life to sports, not just as an athlete but as a member of the International Olympic Committee, which she joined in 1986, the first Black person and the first woman to do so.\", \"from\": 7762, \"to\": 7962, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7851, \"end\": 7882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"DeFrantz\", \"from\": 7762, \"to\": 7770}, {\"ngram\": \"her life\", \"from\": 7785, \"to\": 7793}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 7797, \"to\": 7803}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 7817, \"to\": 7827}, {\"ngram\": \"a member\", \"from\": 7835, \"to\": 7843}, {\"ngram\": \"the first Black person\", \"from\": 7910, \"to\": 7932}, {\"ngram\": \"the first woman\", \"from\": 7937, \"to\": 7952}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She wrote a memoir calledMy Olympic Life.\", \"from\": 7963, \"to\": 8004, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a memoir calledMy Olympic Life\", \"from\": 7973, \"to\": 8003}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But DeFrantz does not seem to care for sports besides the niche Olympic ones.\", \"from\": 8005, \"to\": 8082, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"DeFrantz\", \"from\": 8009, \"to\": 8017}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 8044, \"to\": 8050}, {\"ngram\": \"the niche Olympic ones\", \"from\": 8059, \"to\": 8081}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When I asked whether she followed any ball sports, she diplomatically said that she rooted for all the professional teams of Los Angeles, where she lives, but has no time to follow them.\", \"from\": 8083, \"to\": 8269, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8208, \"end\": 8219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.752010682835559e-18, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any ball sports\", \"from\": 8117, \"to\": 8132}, {\"ngram\": \"all the professional teams\", \"from\": 8178, \"to\": 8204}, {\"ngram\": \"no time\", \"from\": 8246, \"to\": 8253}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I found her indifference inspiring.\", \"from\": 8270, \"to\": 8305, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her indifference\", \"from\": 8278, \"to\": 8294}]}, {\"sen